author: Inside Edition
description: Police say parents took a walk down the beach with three of their children, leaving their 6-month-old girl alone in a tent. A woman who was nearby says when she saw the baby alone she notified hotel staff and called 911. By the time deputies arrived, hotel personnel said the baby had been left unattended for 56 minutes. The dad told cops that "they lost track of time and did not realize how long they had been gone," the police report says. The parents have been charged with child neglect.
title: Parents Charged After Leaving Infant On Beach For Nearly An Hour: Cops

author: Inside Edition
description: The East Wing of the White House got demolished, and it's sparking outrage Tuesday. On TV, President Donald Trump's biggest critics are weighing in, but Trump is unapologetic. In fact, he's delighted. The First Lady's office and her staff have been moved out and all White House tours, which start at the east wing, have been indefinitely suspended. It's all being replaced by a massive ballroom. Inside Edition's Les Trent is at the White House.
title: White House Demolition Sparks Outrage

author: Inside Edition
description: America is being hit by a wave of pumpkin porch pirate heists. Jess Groleau says someone absconded with two pumpkins that her daughter, Leah, had grown on the family's property in Michigan. The mother says the day after she posted the video of the pumpkins being stolen, the man who took the pumpkins brought them back, looked into the camera and apologized. With all the Halloween heists, one police department advised people to keep an eye on jack-o’-lanterns and consider securing them.
title: Porch Pirate Caught Swiping Pumpkins From Family Home

author: Inside Edition
description: Kari Thorp noticed smoke and flames under the hood of the school bus after her daughter was dropped off from school. Ring camera video shows the fire building. Thorp sprang into action to get the kids off the bus in front of her house in Bethel, Minnesota. All 22 kids were led away from the porch and down the block to get them as far away from the bus as possible in case it exploded. Black smoke and flames engulfed the bus. The bus driver and Thorp are being hailed as heroes.
title: Hero Mom And Bus Driver Save Kids Before Fire Engulfs Bus

author: Inside Edition
description: Shannon Keeler was raped in 2013 when she was a college freshman. A junior followed her back to her dorm after a party and forced his way into her room. At the time, Keeler went to the police hoping they would pursue charges against her attacker, Ian Cleary. Nearly seven years passed. Then, out of nowhere, Keeler received incriminating messages on Facebook from her assailant. Cleary has pleaded guilty to sexual assault. On Monday, he was sentenced to 2 to 4 years behind bars.
title: Man Sentenced In Rape Case Years After Sending Chilling Message

author: Inside Edition
description: An American chess Grandmaster has died. Daniel Naroditsky, an accomplished player and teacher with the Charlotte Chess Center, passed away unexpectedly, according to the organization. Aside from teaching at the center, he had a YouTube channel where he taught to anyone willing to tune in. Condolences have been pouring in from the international chess community. Daniel Naroditsky was 29. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Chess Grandmaster Daniel Naroditsky Has Died At 29

author: Inside Edition
description: Kayakers at Silver Springs State Park were left stunned when dozens of rhesus macaques suddenly started leaping into the river.
title: Why Was It Raining Monkeys? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: The Secret Service says it discovered a "hunting stand" in a tree near West Palm Beach Airport with a "direct line of sight" to where Air Force One sits when President Donald Trump visits.
title: Hunting Stand Found Near Trump's Air Force Landing Exit #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A family desperately searched for their beloved Shih Tzu, Princess, in New Jersey. The little dog ran away from the house when the front door was open. She raced across the yard and crossed a busy road. Her owner, Isabella Siqueira, tells Inside Edition's Ann Mercogliano that it happened in a split second. The family used their rottweiler named Dimba as a search dog. Dimba traced the scent to a neighbor's property but found nothing. Later that day, the neighbor spotted Princess by his house.
title: Family Reunites With Their Beloved Missing Dog, Princess

author: Inside Edition
description: These homeowners say at least 13 people have been found dead in the 200-year-old history of the house. The mansion in St. Louis is one of the five finalists in the HGTV show "Scariest House in America," hosted by actress and comedian Retta. Aleha Jane and Kyle Wheeler say baffling happenings are commonplace. The Wheelers will find out if they own the scariest house in America when HGTV airs the season finale on Friday.
title: Is This The Scariest House In America?
